+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PnnpLJagWMLCk6CweQP7BV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide a comprehensive summary.\n\n---\n\n## Event-Driven Order Processing System - Complete Codebase Analysis\n\n### Project Overview\nThis is a TypeScript-based event-driven order processing system implementing a full order lifecycle with event-driven architecture. It uses Vitest for testing and follows strict TypeScript compilation rules.\n\n---\n\n### SOURCE FILES STRUCTURE (`/workspace/src/`)\n\n#### 1. **Core Event Bus** (`/workspace/src/events/`)\n\n**`/workspace/src/events/types.ts`** - Event type definitions\n- Defines all event interfaces for the order processing workflow\n- Exports `ORDER_EVENTS` constant with event type strings:\n  - `order.created`, `order.confirmed`, `order.cancelled`, `order.refunded`\n  - `order.payment.charged`, `order.stock.reserved`, `order.stock.released`\n  - `order.notification.sent`\n- Event interfaces: `OrderCreatedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent`, `OrderRefundedEvent`, `PaymentChargedEvent`, `StockReservedEvent`\n\n**`/workspace/src/events/bus.ts`** - Publish/Subscribe Event Bus\n- `EventBus` class implementing event-driven communication\n- Uses module-level global `globalHandlers` Map for storing handlers\n- Methods: `on()` (subscribe), `off()` (unsubscribe), `emit()` (publish), `clear()`\n- Supports async event handlers\n\n#### 2. **Orders Module** (`/workspace/src/orders/`)\n\n**`/workspace/src/orders/repository.ts`** - Order Data Layer\n- `Order` interface: id, customerId, items, status (pending|confirmed|cancelled|refunded), total, discount, taxRate, createdAt, updatedAt, notes\n- `OrderItem` interface: productId, quantity, unitPrice\n- `OrderRepository` class with in-memory Map storage:\n  - `create()`, `findById()`, `update()`, `findByCustomer()`, `findByStatus()`, `clear()`\n\n**`/workspace/src/orders/service.ts`** - Order Business Logic\n- `OrderService` class orchestrating order lifecycle\n- Dependencies: OrderRepository, EventBus, BillingService\n- Methods:\n  - `createOrder()` - creates order, emits `order.created`, charges payment via BillingService, emits `order.confirmed`\n  - `cancelOrder()` - cancels confirmed orders, emits `order.cancelled`\n  - `refundOrder()` - refunds cancelled orders within 30-day window, emits `order.refunded`\n  - `getOrder()`, `getOrdersByCustomer()`\n\n#### 3. **Inventory Module** (`/workspace/src/inventory/`)\n\n**`/workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts`** - Stock Data Layer\n- `StockRecord` interface: productId, available (quantity), reserved (quantity)\n- `InventoryRepository` class:\n  - `setStock()`, `getStock()`\n  - `reserve()` - moves items from available to reserved\n  - `release()` - moves items from reserved to available\n  - `clear()`\n\n**`/workspace/src/inventory/service.ts`** - Stock Management Service\n- `InventoryService` class listening to order events\n- Dependencies: InventoryRepository, EventBus\n- Methods:\n  - `registerHandlers()` - subscribes to `order.created` and `order.cancelled`\n  - `handleOrderCreated()` - reserves stock for all items, rolls back on failure, emits `order.stock.reserved`\n  - `handleOrderCancelled()` - releases stock, emits `order.stock.released`\n  - `setStock()`, `getStock()`\n\n#### 4. **Billing Module** (`/workspace/src/billing/`)\n\n**`/workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts`** - Price Calculation Logic\n- `PriceBreakdown` interface: subtotal, discountAmount, taxAmount, total\n- `calculateOrderTotal()` function:\n  - Applies percentage discount to subtotal\n  - Applies tax to discounted amount\n  - Proper rounding to 2 decimal places\n\n**`/workspace/src/billing/service.ts`** - Payment Processing\n- `PaymentRecord` interface: orderId, amount, method, status (charged|refunded), processedAt\n- `BillingService` class:\n  - Dependencies: EventBus, NotificationService\n  - Methods:\n    - `registerHandlers()` - subscribes to `order.stock.reserved` and `order.refunded`\n    - `chargePayment()` - calculates total and records payment, sends confirmation notification\n    - `issueRefund()` - marks payment as refunded, emits `order.refunded`\n    - `getPayment()`, `clear()`\n  - In-memory Map storage for payments\n\n#### 5. **Notifications Module** (`/workspace/src/notifications/`)\n\n**`/workspace/src/notifications/service.ts`** - Notification Service\n- `NotificationRecord` interface: type, orderId, message, sentAt\n- `NotificationService` class:\n  - Template-based notification system (stored in Map)\n  - Methods:\n    - `sendConfirmation()` - order confirmation with total\n    - `sendCancellation()` - cancellation notice with reason\n    - `sendRefundNotice()` - refund notification with amount\n    - `getSentNotifications()`, `clear()`\n  - Supports template interpolation: {orderId}, {reason}, {total}, {amount}\n\n#### 6. **Main Export** (`/workspace/src/index.ts`)\n- Re-exports all public APIs from modules\n- Exports types and classes for consumer usage\n\n---\n\n### TEST FILES STRUCTURE (`/workspace/tests/`)\n\n**Total: 5 test files with 30+ visible tests**\n\n#### **`/workspace/tests/events.test.ts`** - Event Bus Tests (5 tests)\n- Event emission and handler registration\n- Multiple handlers per event\n- Handler removal with `off()`\n- Event clearing with `clear()`\n\n#### **`/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts`** - Order Service & Repository Tests (16 tests)\n- Order creation and confirmation\n- Stock reservation on creation\n- Order cancellation and stock release\n- Refund processing with 30-day window validation\n- Repository CRUD operations and filtering\n\n#### **`/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts`** - Inventory Service Tests (6 tests)\n- Stock reservation on order creation\n- Rollback on insufficient stock\n- Stock release on cancellation\n- Concurrent order handling\n\n#### **`/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts`** - Billing Service & Calculator Tests (8 tests)\n- Price calculation with discount and tax\n- Rounding precision\n- Payment charging and refunds\n- Notification integration\n\n#### **`/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts`** - Notification Service Tests (4 tests)\n- Confirmation, cancellation, and refund notifications\n- Notification tracking\n\n---\n\n### ARCHITECTURE & MODULE CONNECTIONS\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       EventBus (Central Hub)                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                    ┌─────────┼─────────┐\n                    │         │         │\n            ┌───────▼──┐ ┌───▼────┐ ┌──▼──────────┐\n            │  Orders  │ │ Billing│ │ Inventory  │\n            │ Service  │ │Service │ │ Service    │\n            └───────┬──┘ └───┬────┘ └──┬──────────┘\n                    │       │         │\n                    └───────┼─────────┘\n                            │\n                    ┌───────▼──────────┐\n                    │ Notifications   │\n                    │ Service         │\n                    └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Data Flow:**\n1. `OrderService.createOrder()` → emits `order.created`\n2. `InventoryService` listens → reserves stock → emits `order.stock.reserved`\n3. `BillingService` → charges payment → sends confirmation notification\n4. On cancellation: `OrderService.cancelOrder()` → emits `order.cancelled`\n5. `InventoryService` releases stock → `BillingService` processes refund → notifications sent\n\n**Cross-Module Dependencies:**\n- OrderService depends on: OrderRepository, EventBus, BillingService\n- InventoryService depends on: InventoryRepository, EventBus\n- BillingService depends on: EventBus, NotificationService\n- All services use EventBus for inter-service communication\n\n---\n\n### KEY CHARACTERISTICS\n\n1. **Event-Driven Architecture**: Loose coupling via EventBus publish/subscribe pattern\n2. **In-Memory Storage**: All repositories use Map-based storage (no persistence)\n3. **Synchronous Event Handlers**: Although `emit()` is async, handlers run sequentially\n4. **Rollback Support**: Inventory service rolls back partial reservations on failure\n5. **Business Rules**:\n   - Refund window: 30 days from order creation\n   - Tax applied after discount\n   - Decimal rounding to 2 places\n6. **Testing Framework**: Vitest with 10-second test timeout\n7. **TypeScript**: Strict mode enabled, Node16 module resolution, ES2022 target\n\n---\n\n### FILE MANIFEST (Complete List)\n\n**Source Files:**\n- /workspace/src/index.ts\n- /workspace/src/events/types.ts\n- /workspace/src/events/bus.ts\n- /workspace/src/orders/repository.ts\n- /workspace/src/orders/service.ts\n- /workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts\n- /workspace/src/inventory/service.ts\n- /workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts\n- /workspace/src/billing/service.ts\n- /workspace/src/notifications/service.ts\n\n**Test Files:**\n- /workspace/tests/events.test.ts\n- /workspace/tests/orders.test.ts\n- /workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts\n- /workspace/tests/billing.test.ts\n- /workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts\n\n**Configuration Files:**\n- /workspace/package.json\n- /workspace/tsconfig.json\n- /workspace/vitest.config.ts\n- /workspace/TASK.md"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adfaf73 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 33297\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 40284</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cad43278-a942-45f4-b28c-fca5abf69607","uuid":"045e5234-e674-413f-b841-a7de183c2596","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full codebase structure of this event-driven order processing system. I need to understand:\n1. All source files under src/ and their purposes\n2. All test files\n3. The overall architecture and how modules connect\n\nList every file with its path. Read the key source files to understand the implementation. Focus on src/ directo